# ============================================================
# Docker build context excludes (PRD 6. fejezet – Docker)
#
# Keeps the build context small and – critically – prevents the
# builder stage `COPY . .` from clobbering the Linux (musl) node_modules
# installed by `npm ci` with host-platform (Windows/macOS) binaries.
# Without this file a local `fly deploy` breaks at the "Build image"
# step because Prisma/Next native binaries end up wrong-platform.
# ============================================================

# Dependencies – reinstalled inside the image via `npm ci`
node_modules
.pnp
.pnp.js

# Next.js build output – regenerated inside the image
.next
out

# Version control / CI
.git
.gitignore
.github
.husky

# Local environment & secrets – never bake into the image
.env
.env.*
!.env.example

# Test / coverage / local tooling
coverage
vitest.config.ts
vitest.setup.ts

# Editor / OS cruft
.vscode
.idea
.DS_Store
*.log
npm-debug.log*

# Docs & compose (not needed at build time)
docker-compose.yml
README.md
PRD.md
docs
